                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Edinburgh was one of the cities I was most looking forward to visiting during our "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "http://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/2015/12/hello-friends-a-big-announcement/",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "big European adventure"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Before visiting, I dreamed of regal castles full of history, charming buildings holding enchanting stories, and romantic streets filled with bagpipe music. That is why I made sure to book one of our longest stays of the whole trip in this city (five days!). I'm happy to say that the image in my head was very accurate, and you definitely need to make sure Edinburgh is on your travel bucket list."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In the descriptions below, I have underlined the attractions, restaurants, and things to do that I suggest adding to your five-day itinerary in Edinburgh based on my experience."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Day 1 - Authentic Scottish Dinner"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Due to flooding in England's Lake District, our trip from "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "http://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/2016/02/travel-with-me-winter-in-englands-lake-district/",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "Ambleside"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to Edinburgh was much longer than it should have been. We had to take a couple of trains and then switch to a bus that replaced the final train of the trip. Needless to say, it was a long day of travel, and we arrived at our hotel in Edinburgh tired and hungry! We decided to find a great Scottish restaurant for our first dinner in Scotland before calling it an early night."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "I have a cousin who went to the University of Edinburgh, and I have her to thank for many of the things we did in Edinburgh, not least of which was eat dinner at "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "strong"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Mums Great Comfort Food"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". If you are looking for a traditional Scottish meal for a good value, look no further! I ordered sausages and mash, and Daniel orded haggis (brave man!). We both loved our dishes, and we had excellent service. The waitresses were happy to give suggestions and even asked us questions about our trip. We loved it!"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "[caption id=\"attachment_5491\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"768\"]"
          },
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/2016-01-09-19.01.31-768x1024.jpg",
              "alt": "2016-01-09 19.01.31",
              "title": null
            },
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "http://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/2016-01-09-19.01.31.jpg",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " Sausages and mash at Mums Great Comfort Food[/caption]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "[caption id=\"attachment_5552\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1024\"]"
          },
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/20160109_190133-1024x576.jpg",
              "alt": "20160109_190133",
              "title": null
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " Daniel's Haggis! If you don't know what haggis is, you can google it, but just know that the true form of haggis isn't even legal in the United States. I couldn't handle it![/caption]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Day 2 - Coffee Shop Hopping"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Our second day in Edinburgh was the first day on our trip where we took a full day to just rest and get caught up on \"work\" (real work for Daniel, blogging for me). We had read about so many great coffee shops in Edinburgh, so we were excited to check some of them out and make them our \"office\" for the day. We ended up trying out three coffee shops because the first didn't have internet, the second had bad internet, and (finally!) the third was the perfect place for us to actually be productive."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Elephant House"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Our first stop was at The Elephant House, a cafe well-known for being the place where J.K. Rowling wrote the first book of the Harry Potter series. We had a delicious breakfast here and enjoyed the coffee and the beautiful environment. While it usually is a good place to get some work done, their internet was broken that day, so we had to move on after finishing our coffees."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/2016-01-10-11.31.16-1024x768.jpg",
              "alt": "2016-01-10 11.31.16",
              "title": null
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "[caption id=\"attachment_5497\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1024\"]"
          },
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/2016-01-10-11.39.37-1024x768.jpg",
              "alt": "2016-01-10 11.39.37",
              "title": null
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " While the Elephant House is definitely proud of their claim to fame, this small plaque of J.K. Rowling pictures was one of the few hints of it. I was happy to see this because it gave the cafe a more authentic feel.[/caption]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Black Medicine Coffee Co."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Black Medicine offered both delicious coffee and a great working environment, but the internet was having issues that day, so once again, we weren't able to stay for long. We enjoyed sitting in the less-crowded basement area."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "[caption id=\"attachment_5499\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1024\"]"
          },
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/2016-01-10-11.54.27-1024x768.jpg",
              "alt": "2016-01-10 11.54.27",
              "title": null
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " Look at this beautiful flat white![/caption]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Brew Lab"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For our final (and favorite) coffee shop stop of the day, we picked Brew Lab. This one stood out to us because while we love a good latte or flat white, we are really filter coffee lovers at heart. Europeans love their espresso and are not very big on filter coffee or pour overs, so we were excited to finally find a place like Brew Lab, which offers a variety of single-origin pour overs."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "[caption id=\"attachment_5501\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1024\"]"
          },
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/2016-01-10-13.22.06-1024x768.jpg",
              "alt": "2016-01-10 13.22.06",
              "title": null
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " Beautiful pour over coffee![/caption]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "After what many would consider to be caffeine over-load and a very productive few hours, we walked around the city at night a little bit, and then called it another early night in preparation for our first full day of sightseeing in Edinburgh the next day."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "[caption id=\"attachment_5502\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1024\"]"
          },
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/2016-01-10-16.33.45-1024x768.jpg",
              "alt": "2016-01-10 16.33.45",
              "title": null
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " See the beautiful Edinburgh Castle at the top of the hill?[/caption]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Day 3 - Royal Edinburgh"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The next morning started out with a slow walk in the city."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "[caption id=\"attachment_5492\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1024\"]"
          },
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/2016-01-10-11.04.43-1024x768.jpg",
              "alt": "2016-01-10 11.04.43",
              "title": null
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " I love the morning light on these buildings.[/caption]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/2016-01-10-11.11.59-1024x768.jpg",
              "alt": "2016-01-10 11.11.59",
              "title": null
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Next we paid a visit to "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "strong"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Edinburgh Castle"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Little did we know that there would be so much to see and do at the castle! It is full of so much history. According to the Castle's website, there has been a royal castle on Castle Rock (Edinburgh Castle's home) since at least the 12th century. St. Margaret's Chapel on the castle grounds was completed in the year 1140 and still stands today as the oldest building at the site. The Scots and the English took turns taking over the castle over the years. Mary Queen of Scots gave birth to her son James VI here. The Crown Jewels of Scotland were lost and found again here. I could go on and on...."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The first thing to do when you arrive is take pictures of the castle and of the gorgeous views of Edinburgh."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
