        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Day 5 - Last Full Day"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "We started out our last full day in Edinburgh in the best way - with cake for breakfast! How delicious does that carrot cake look? Please do me a favor and check out "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "strong"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Lovecrumbs"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " on your trip to Edinburgh!"
          },
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/2016-01-13-12.03.07-1024x768.jpg",
              "alt": "2016-01-13 12.03.07",
              "title": null
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "We then made our way over to the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "strong"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Royal Yacht Britannia"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". We had heard great things about the exhibit from both TripAdvisor and from Edinburgh locals, so we decided to do it even though the admission price was a little high. We ended up really enjoying it and learning a lot about the royal family. Visitors walk through the actual yacht with an audioguide telling you all kinds of interesting information about this yacht that served the royal famiy for forty-four years. I'd also like to point out that this exhibit is perfect for kids."
          }
        ]
